<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>94<percent/> of 49</li> 
<li>3<percent/> of 2696</li> 
<li>31<percent/> of 221</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 3<percent/> of 2696</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{94}\%\cdot{49}={46.06}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{31}\%\cdot{221}={68.51}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}\%\cdot{2696}={80.88}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 3<percent/> of 2696 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
